==English==

===Entymology===
Middle English - [[saysen]] or [[seysen]], meaning to [[seize]].
Old French - [[seisir]] or [[saisir]] which is from the low latin word [[sacire]], generally referred to the same source as Goth [[satjan]] and Old English [[settan]].

===Noun===
